  "notes": "Locked grading artifact for semantic action clustering (cluster-2.0). Each case asks: do actions a and b denote the same real-world act by the same actor toward the same target? 'same' = objectively the same act; 'different' = objectively materially different acts or targets; 'unresolved' = genuinely undecidable from the given information (e.g. an irreducibly ambiguous target). Do not edit: tests pin this file by SHA-256.",
  "cases": [
    {
      "id": "exact_accept_same",
      "a": {"action_name": "accept", "target": "board"},
      "b": {"action_name": "accept", "target": "board"},
      "known_entities": ["board"],
      "expected": "same",
      "why": "Identical ontology action and identical canonical target."
    },
    {
